omp is Copyright (C) 2007-2014 Charles E. Hawkins

omp has only been tested on Linux--Arch and Ubuntu.

omp is a graphical utility to play ogg, mp3, flac, mp4, flv, mov, m4a,
avi, and mod files according to a rating system designed to keep track
of user listening habits.  The idea was inspired by vux.  I also wanted
a player that uses little memory so program features have been kept to
a minimum.

omp requires OTk to build and vlc to run.  Arch users can find OTk
in the AUR package ocaml-otk.  Others can find it at:
forge.ocamlcore.org/projects/otk
vlc should be readily available as a package on any distribution.


A few of the changes from vux:
  1. Added GUI.  omp was designed to run using both an xterm and a GUI.
  2. Rating is simply a percentage chance of playing.
  3. Added ability to modify playlist and configuration while program is
     running.
  4. Added ability to play many other file types.
  5. Added ability to manually queue files for playing.

See INSTALL for instructions on how to build and install omp.

Please read the "Credits" section of the user manual.
